@@yCLANS@@g

Clans are player-run political organizations on Shades of Evil. Each clan
has its own identity, leadership, and standing in the world. Clan membership
is visible in @@ywho@@g, @@yscore@@g, and @@yfinger@@g.

A player may belong to one clan, one @@ypublic society@@g, and one
@@ysecret society@@g at the same time. These three affiliation systems are
independent of each other.

@@yCLAN MEMBERSHIP@@g

Clan membership is managed by immortals using the @@ycset@@g command.
Contact the staff if you wish to join or leave a clan.

Your clan affiliation grants you @@yclan colors@@g — a wearable item bearing
your clan's emblem. Use @@yclaneq@@g to choose the stat focus of your colors:

  @@yclaneq melee@@g    -- Optimized for melee fighters (hitroll, damroll)
  @@yclaneq caster@@g   -- Optimized for spellcasters (mana, spell stats)
  @@yclaneq tank@@g     -- Optimized for defensive roles (HP, armor)

@@yCLAN CHANNEL@@g

  @@yclan <message>@@g  -- Sends a message to all online clan members

@@yCLAN COMMANDS@@g

  @@yclan <message>@@g  -- Speak on the clan communication channel
  @@yclaneq <style>@@g  -- Set your clan colors to melee, caster, or tank
  @@yclist@@g           -- List all clans and basic clan information
  @@yhome@@g            -- Recall directly to your clan headquarters
  @@yleave@@g           -- Voluntarily depart from your clan

@@yOTHER AFFILIATIONS@@g

Beyond clans, two additional affiliation systems exist:

  @@yPublic Societies@@g -- Open civic institutions (Guard Command, Harbor
    Syndics, Ember Wardens, Shrine of the First Claw, Wall Command, Road
    Wardens). Membership is visible, open to qualified applicants, and grants
    rank-gated skills and task-board missions. Use @@yenlist@@g at a society
    hall to join. A player may belong to one public society at a time.

  @@ySecret Societies@@g -- Hidden covert organizations (The Reckoning, The
    Jade Eels, The Ash Cult, The Quiet Hand, The Jackal Synod, The Pale
    Ledger). Membership is concealed from public commands. Discovery requires
    finding the right contacts in the world. A player may belong to one
    secret society at a time.

